The paper deals with beamforming control for video streaming applications in a multi-antenna interference network, which involves techniques from information theory (cs.IT), networking (cs.NI), control theory (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and game theory (cs.GT). The abstract mentions the use of heavy traffic approximation technique, which is commonly used in queuing theory and stochastic processes (cs.PR). However, since the focus of the paper is on the application of these techniques to a specific problem in wireless networks, we consider cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, and cs.GT to be the most likely sub-categories.
